            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>marinated tofu </strong>and cook for 6-7 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4 or more? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670922933988-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670922933988-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670922933988-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670922933988-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670922933988-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into matchsticks</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>pho broth paste</strong>, <strong>umami seasoning </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[800ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>pho stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670922943169-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670922943169-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670922943169-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670922943169-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1670922943169-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your<strong> lime[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Strip most of your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, leave some on the stems</p><p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1670922952093-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1670922952093-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1670922952093-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1670922952093-x1000.jpg",
